            . I am an <rs id="t18091206-78-viclabel466" type="occupation">umbrella maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18091206-78-victim664 t18091206-78-viclabel466"></join>, <placeName id="t18091206-78-crimeloc467">40, Hay-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18091206-78-crimeloc467" type="placeName" value="40, Hay-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18091206-78-crimeloc467" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18091206-78-off464 t18091206-78-crimeloc467"></join>. On the 20th of November, in the evening, about six o'clock, I saw the prisoner pass my shop; he made a spring in the shop, seized an umbrella, and immediately run off with it, and I after him. At the corner of Coventry-street, he threw the umbrella out of his hands; I pursued him, and took him, and collared him; he said, he had done nothing. I took him back to my shop. A young man picked up my umbrella, he gave it me; I knew it to be my property.</p>
               <p>The property produced and identified.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in his defence; called three witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18091206-78-verdict468" type="verdictDescription">
